07447nam a22010215i 9789814380461DE-B159720221201113901.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||221201t20122012si     fo  d z      eng d  a2012330775  a97898143804617 a10.1355/97898143804612doi  a(DE-B1597)491780  a(OCoLC)1041982691  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  asicSG00aJV8490b.M533 2013 4aJV8490b.M536 2015 7aSOC0070002bisacsh04a304.809522300aMigration and Diversity in Asian Contexts /ced. by Lai Ah Eng, Francis Leo Collins, Brenda Yeoh Saw Ai. 1aSingapore : bISEAS Publishing, c[2012] 4cÂ©2012  a1 online resource (308 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tlist of contributors -- tACKNOWLEDGEMENTs -- tINTRODUCTION. Approaching Migration and Diversity in Asian Contexts -- tI. Migration, Multiculturalism and Governance in Asia -- t1. Multicultural Realities and Membership: States, Migrations and Citizenship in Asia -- t2. Multicultural Coexistence Policies of Local Governments in the Tokyo Metropolis: A Comparative Examination of Social Integration in Response to Growing Ethnic Diversity -- t3. The Place of Migrant Workers in Singapore: Between State Multiracialism and Everyday (Un)Cosmopolitanisms -- t4. Selective State Response and Ethnic Minority Incorporation: The South Korean Case -- t5. The Tug of War over Multiculturalism: Contestation between Governing and Empowering Immigrants in Taiwan -- tII. Identities -- t6. Mixed-ethnic Children Raised by Single Thai Mothers in Japan: A Choice of Ethnic Identity -- t7. Being Indian in Post-colonial Metro Manila: Identities, Boundaries and the Media Practices -- tIII. Practices -- t8. The Kopitiam in Singapore: An Evolving Story about Migration and Cultural Diversity -- t9. Spatial Process and Cultural Territory of Islamic Food Restaurants in Itaewon, Seoul -- t10. Competition and Constructedness: Sports, Migration and Diversity in Singapore -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThis volume makes an important and unique contribution to scholarly understandings of migration and diversity through its focus on Asian contexts. Current scholarship and literature on processes of migration and the consequences of diversity is heavily concentrated on Western contexts and their concerns with "multiculturalism", "integration", "rights and responsibilities", "social cohesion", "social inclusion", and "cosmopolitanism". In contrast, there has been relatively little attention given to migration and growing diversity in Asian contexts which are constituted by highly distinct and varied histories, cultures, geographies, and political economies. This book fills this significant gap in the literature on migration studies with a concentrated focus on communities, cities and countries in the Asian region that are experiencing increased levels of population mobility and subsequent diversity. Not only does it offer analyses of the policies and processes of migration, it also addresses the outcomes and implications of migration and diversity - these include a focus on multiculturalism and citizenship in the Asian region, the emerging complex forms of governance in response to increased diversity, discussions of different settlement experiences, and the practices of everyday life and encounters in increasingly diverse locales.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aAsia--Emigration and immigration. 0aEthnicityzAsia. 0aEthnicity--Asia. 0aMulticulturalismzAsia. 0aMulticulturalism--Asia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Emigration & Immigration.2bisacsh1 aAh Eng, Lai, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aAsis, Maruja M.B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aB